Always has the food hot and ready. great place to sit and eat or take home. the T.v. always on something good may it be sports or my favorite Law and Order Svu. Cas the owner has great enthusiasm always has a time for a joke and laugh... I've Been going here for  about 13 years and my son who is 6 loves the plantains and the little cakes. I love EVERYTHING lol from the soups to the codfish, the oxtails are always on point,jerk chicken never dry and oh its sooo flavorful, corn meal porridge is the best on cold days.. and the cow foot soup is Yesssssssssssss I can eat that in 90 degrees that's how good it is. If you want that family /island vibe where you can chill and even grab a beer watch t.v and talk some good good conversation with anyone who walks in.. this and will always be the place to go.. Its safe and the people in the neighborhood are friendly and watch over this family restaurant.
